11#ifndef MODULES_AUDIO_CODING_NETEQ_DECISION_LOGIC_H_
12#define MODULES_AUDIO_CODING_NETEQ_DECISION_LOGIC_H_
13
14#include <memory>
15
16#include "api/neteq/neteq.h"
17#include "api/neteq/neteq_controller.h"
18#include "api/neteq/tick_timer.h"
19#include "modules/audio_coding/neteq/buffer_level_filter.h"
20#include "modules/audio_coding/neteq/delay_manager.h"
21#include "rtc_base/constructor_magic.h"
22#include "rtc_base/experiments/field_trial_parser.h"
23
24namespace webrtc {
25
26// This is the class for the decision tree implementation.
27class DecisionLogic : public NetEqController {
28 public:
29 static const int kReinitAfterExpands = 100;
30 static const int kMaxWaitForPacket = 10;
31
32 // Constructor.
33 DecisionLogic(NetEqController::Config config);
34 DecisionLogic(NetEqController::Config config,
35 std::unique_ptr<DelayManager> delay_manager,
36 std::unique_ptr<BufferLevelFilter> buffer_level_filter);
37
38 ~DecisionLogic() override;
39
40 // Resets object to a clean state.
41 void Reset() override;
42
43 // Resets parts of the state. Typically done when switching codecs.
44 void SoftReset() override;
45
46 // Sets the sample rate and the output block size.
47 void SetSampleRate(int fs_hz, size_t output_size_samples) override;
48
49 // Given info about the latest received packet, and current jitter buffer
50 // status, returns the operation. |target_timestamp| and |expand_mutefactor|
51 // are provided for reference. |last_packet_samples| is the number of samples
52 // obtained from the last decoded frame. If there is a packet available, it
53 // should be supplied in |packet|; otherwise it should be NULL. The mode
54 // resulting from the last call to NetEqImpl::GetAudio is supplied in
55 // |last_mode|. If there is a DTMF event to play, |play_dtmf| should be set to
56 // true. The output variable |reset_decoder| will be set to true if a reset is
57 // required; otherwise it is left unchanged (i.e., it can remain true if it
58 // was true before the call).
59 NetEq::Operation GetDecision(const NetEqController::NetEqStatus& status,
60 bool* reset_decoder) override;
61
62 // These methods test the |cng_state_| for different conditions.
63 bool CngRfc3389On() const override { return cng_state_ == kCngRfc3389On; }
64 bool CngOff() const override { return cng_state_ == kCngOff; }
65
66 // Resets the |cng_state_| to kCngOff.
67 void SetCngOff() override { cng_state_ = kCngOff; }
68
69 // Reports back to DecisionLogic whether the decision to do expand remains or
70 // not. Note that this is necessary, since an expand decision can be changed
71 // to kNormal in NetEqImpl::GetDecision if there is still enough data in the
72 // sync buffer.
73 void ExpandDecision(NetEq::Operation operation) override;
74
75 // Adds |value| to |sample_memory_|.
76 void AddSampleMemory(int32_t value) override { sample_memory_ += value; }
77
78 int TargetLevelMs() const override { return delay_manager_->TargetDelayMs(); }
79
80 absl::optional<int> PacketArrived(int fs_hz,
81 bool should_update_stats,
82 const PacketArrivedInfo& info) override;
83
84 void RegisterEmptyPacket() override {}
85
86 void NotifyMutedState() override {}
87
88 bool SetMaximumDelay(int delay_ms) override {
89 return delay_manager_->SetMaximumDelay(delay_ms);
90 }
91 bool SetMinimumDelay(int delay_ms) override {
92 return delay_manager_->SetMinimumDelay(delay_ms);
93 }
94 bool SetBaseMinimumDelay(int delay_ms) override {
95 return delay_manager_->SetBaseMinimumDelay(delay_ms);
96 }
97 int GetBaseMinimumDelay() const override {
98 return delay_manager_->GetBaseMinimumDelay();
99 }
100 bool PeakFound() const override { return false; }
101
102 int GetFilteredBufferLevel() const override {
103 return buffer_level_filter_->filtered_current_level();
104 }
105
106 // Accessors and mutators.
107 void set_sample_memory(int32_t value) override { sample_memory_ = value; }
108 size_t noise_fast_forward() const override { return noise_fast_forward_; }
109 size_t packet_length_samples() const override {
110 return packet_length_samples_;
111 }
112 void set_packet_length_samples(size_t value) override {
113 packet_length_samples_ = value;
114 }
115 void set_prev_time_scale(bool value) override { prev_time_scale_ = value; }
116
117 private:
118 // The value 5 sets maximum time-stretch rate to about 100 ms/s.
119 static const int kMinTimescaleInterval = 5;
120
121 enum CngState { kCngOff, kCngRfc3389On, kCngInternalOn };
122
123 // Updates the |buffer_level_filter_| with the current buffer level
124 // |buffer_size_samples|.
125 void FilterBufferLevel(size_t buffer_size_samples);
126
127 // Returns the operation given that the next available packet is a comfort
128 // noise payload (RFC 3389 only, not codec-internal).
129 virtual NetEq::Operation CngOperation(NetEq::Mode prev_mode,
130 uint32_t target_timestamp,
131 uint32_t available_timestamp,
132 size_t generated_noise_samples);
133
134 // Returns the operation given that no packets are available (except maybe
135 // a DTMF event, flagged by setting |play_dtmf| true).
136 virtual NetEq::Operation NoPacket(bool play_dtmf);
137
138 // Returns the operation to do given that the expected packet is available.
139 virtual NetEq::Operation ExpectedPacketAvailable(NetEq::Mode prev_mode,
140 bool play_dtmf);
141
142 // Returns the operation to do given that the expected packet is not
143 // available, but a packet further into the future is at hand.
144 virtual NetEq::Operation FuturePacketAvailable(
145 size_t decoder_frame_length,
146 NetEq::Mode prev_mode,
147 uint32_t target_timestamp,
148 uint32_t available_timestamp,
149 bool play_dtmf,
150 size_t generated_noise_samples,
151 size_t span_samples_in_packet_buffer,
152 size_t num_packets_in_packet_buffer);
153
154 // Checks if enough time has elapsed since the last successful timescale
155 // operation was done (i.e., accelerate or preemptive expand).
156 bool TimescaleAllowed() const {
157 return !timescale_countdown_ || timescale_countdown_->Finished();
158 }
159
160 // Checks if the current (filtered) buffer level is under the target level.
161 bool UnderTargetLevel() const;
162
163 // Checks if |timestamp_leap| is so long into the future that a reset due
164 // to exceeding kReinitAfterExpands will be done.
165 bool ReinitAfterExpands(uint32_t timestamp_leap) const;
166
167 // Checks if we still have not done enough expands to cover the distance from
168 // the last decoded packet to the next available packet, the distance beeing
169 // conveyed in |timestamp_leap|.
170 bool PacketTooEarly(uint32_t timestamp_leap) const;
171
172 // Checks if num_consecutive_expands_ >= kMaxWaitForPacket.
173 bool MaxWaitForPacket() const;
174
175 std::unique_ptr<DelayManager> delay_manager_;
176 std::unique_ptr<BufferLevelFilter> buffer_level_filter_;
177 const TickTimer* tick_timer_;
178 int sample_rate_;
179 size_t output_size_samples_;
180 CngState cng_state_ = kCngOff; // Remember if comfort noise is interrupted by
181 // other event (e.g., DTMF).
182 size_t noise_fast_forward_ = 0;
183 size_t packet_length_samples_ = 0;
184 int sample_memory_ = 0;
185 bool prev_time_scale_ = false;
186 bool disallow_time_stretching_;
187 std::unique_ptr<TickTimer::Countdown> timescale_countdown_;
188 int num_consecutive_expands_ = 0;
189 int time_stretched_cn_samples_ = 0;
190 bool last_pack_cng_or_dtmf_ = true;
191 bool buffer_flush_ = false;
192 FieldTrialParameter<bool> estimate_dtx_delay_;
193 FieldTrialParameter<bool> time_stretch_cn_;
194 FieldTrialConstrained<int> target_level_window_ms_;
195
196 RTC_DISALLOW_COPY_AND_ASSIGN(DecisionLogic);
197};
198
199} // namespace webrtc
200#endif // MODULES_AUDIO_CODING_NETEQ_DECISION_LOGIC_H_
